[Weekly Briefing] VIR - North - 2017s2 Week 5
[size=18][i][b]Welcome to the SRF![/b][/size]
We pride ourselves on a friendly, competitive and yet relaxed atmosphere both on and off-track. Don't be afraid to ask for help, either in practice sessions or on the forum![/i]

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2466930.page[/img]

[color=red][size=18]Spec Racer Ford Challenge Series @ [b] Virginia International Raceway (VIR) - North[/b]
Week 5 of 12 - 2017 Season 2 [/size][/color]
Race Distance: [b]15 laps[/b], approximately 25 minutes
World Record lap time (qualifying): [b]1:36.187[/b] by David Gaspers
(n.b. random/dynamic weather impacts lap times greatly)

This week we are back state side with a trip to the VIR North Circuit. This track can be challenging with some very fast sections and demanding corner complexes. Especially watch out over the back of the course through the sweepers down hill and expect to find quite a few people grass tracking off the circuit on the last corner. Participation here can be not so good, so please help others out by registering for races earleier rather than later! This way we get the best chance for official sessions.

Target "planned" SoF race is usually 20:45 GMT Sunday, immediately following the Weekend Warriors league race.

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2466931.page[/img]

